      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WESTBOUND (6) resumes today and showed plenty of talent in his debut campaign, winning in a photo finish over the mile at this course before the break. He's an exciting gelding on the way up and his recent trial under CJP was good. Maps beautifully today and can pick up from where he left off. DESERT WAVES (5) stuck on well to finish 1L off the winner last start in a race that's turned into a strong form reference. There's been 4 winners from 7 starters since and he jumped the race favourite on that occasion. He's building nicely and ticks plenty of boxes again today. DON'T TRUST JUDAS (1) flew home over this course and distance last time out to score by 0.6L. Steve Parnham remains in the saddle and he beat home DESERT WAVES two back. Can be in the finish again. PLAYING GAMES (4) gets the blinkers on now and can be in the finish.",
